TITLE: Protests erupt as French government forces through higher retirement age
SUMMARY: The French government has forced through controversial plans to raise the country's retirement age from 62 to 64, a move likely to inflame the country's weeks-long protest movement.

TITLE: Unlike last year, this tax season has been going smoothly
SUMMARY: The past two tax-filing seasons were fraught with aggravations, delays, last-minute changes and huge backlogs at the IRS. But by comparison, this year's tax-filing season has been going relatively smoothly, tax preparers say.

TITLE: Cyclone Freddy survivors dig with bare hands for victims as death toll reaches 326
SUMMARY: Tropical Cyclone Freddy has killed at least 326 people after it ripped through southern Malawi, the country's Department of Disaster Management Affairs told CNN Thursday.

TITLE: Google will stop selling Glass as it looks to cut costs
SUMMARY: Google will no longer sell the latest Enterprise Edition of Google Glass, the company announced this week, effectively killing off an innovative but failed wearable product line from another era that many consumers may have assumed was long gone.

TITLE: 3 Virginia hospital workers charged with murder in death of Irvo Otieno
SUMMARY: Three hospital employees in Virginia were arrested Thursday and charged with second-degree murder in the death of Irvo Otieno, the 28-year-old Black man who died at a state mental health facility last week, the Office of the Commonwealth's Attorney for Dinwiddie County said in a news release obtained by CNN affiliate WTVR.

TITLE: Former UGA football star Jalen Carter sentenced to probation in crash that killed teammate and team staffer, his attorney says
SUMMARY: Former University of Georgia football standout Jalen Carter was sentenced to probation on Thursday for his role in the crash that killed his teammate and a team staffer, his attorney told CNN.

TITLE: Mortgage rates drop in wake of bank failures
SUMMARY: Mortgage rates dropped this week in the wake of several bank failures, reversing course after rising half a percentage point over the past month. But longer-term uncertainty is expected to hamper many homebuyers and keep the cost of buying unaffordable for many.

TITLE: Anastasia Potapova: Russian tennis player 'formally warned' by WTA for wearing Moscow soccer jersey
SUMMARY: The Women's Tennis Association (WTA) has "formally warned" Russian tennis player Anastasia Potapova after she was seen wearing a Spartak Moscow soccer jersey ahead of her match against American Jessica Pegula at Indian Wells, a spokesperson told CNN Thursday.

TITLE: Credit Suisse still has a fight on its hands despite $54 billion lifeline

TITLE: European Central Bank sticks to its rate-hiking guns, says banks 'resilient'
SUMMARY: The European Central Bank (ECB) stuck with its plan to hike interest rates by half a percentage point Thursday, judging that inflation poses a bigger immediate threat to the economy than turmoil in the banking sector.

TITLE: At least 4 Palestinians killed in IDF operation in Jenin
SUMMARY: At least four Palestinians were killed on Thursday and 23 others injured after an Israeli Defense Forces (IDF) operation in Jenin, in the occupied West Bank, according to the Palestinian Authority Health Ministry. At least five of the injured are in critical condition, the health ministry added.
